# Your rule content

In this project, we have exercises located at src/app/(exercises)

In this folder group you will find exercises folders for each lesson, when creating excercises we should do it in a similar format to Kent C Dodds Epic React course, where we use JS Doc at the top of the file to explaint o the user what they need to do and any extra credits / resources, and we should also guide the user with comments on where they should do things

Each exercise will contain partially built out pages where the users will have to edit them to learn how to get to the solution. 

We should also create a solutions file or folder if there are multiple pages that need soultions called solutions.tsx that sits in the same folder as the exercise, this is a completed version of the exercise with no comments, the idea is that if a user is stuck or just wants to compare their solution with the correct one, they can open the solutions file to compare


When we create a new excercise we need to update the constants.ts file

You must add:

- EXERCISE_URLS - The path to the physical exercise files in the editor
- EXERCISE_ROUTES - The url for the web page i.e /server-components
